<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-zD2y8G1WS02QCg5WGdeoMw" name="Refine System design to HW and SW level,_pRw2sJzdEeCBU9GxbrSLZw" guid="-zD2y8G1WS02QCg5WGdeoMw" changeDate="2012-11-13T10:06:15.560-0800" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task is a continuance of the development of the system design down to the HW and SW level.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The nature of the system design can be model based.&amp;nbsp;This is an appropriate medium for a number of methods that can&#xD;
    be used to verify the systems design, which are recommended or highly recommended&amp;nbsp;according to the applied ASIL&#xD;
    level. These methods include system design inspection, system design walk-throughs, simulation, and safety analysis.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If a model based approach is developed further, with the appropriate tools it is possible that system prototyping and&#xD;
    vehicle tests can also be carried out.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The use of a model based approach at this level is especially useful for helping develop the item and integration test&#xD;
    plans.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This could be considered to be a variant on the architectural analysis phase of system development detailed&amp;nbsp;in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20uc_E8CAF5DD.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_H1zdAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Use-Case based&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20op_54664526.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_E9oWAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Operation based&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;depending upon the approach being&#xD;
    taken.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To determine how the system design is to be implemented by HW and SW.&amp;nbsp; This task&amp;nbsp;can be&amp;nbsp;dependent upon ASIL&#xD;
decomposition if applied.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
